{"content":"<header>\n            <small>Getting started<\/small>\n        <h1>Creating a project<\/h1>\n<\/header><ul class=\"toc\"><li>\n        <a href=\"#command-line-helper\">\n            <span class=\"title\">Command line helper<\/span>\n        <\/a>\n            <\/li>\n    <li>\n        <a href=\"#structure\">\n            <span class=\"title\">Structure<\/span>\n        <\/a>\n            <\/li>\n    <li>\n        <a href=\"#minimum-required-files\">\n            <span class=\"title\">Minimum required files<\/span>\n        <\/a>\n                    <ul class=\"sub-menu\">\n                <li>\n        <a href=\"#configphp\">\n            <span class=\"title\">config.php<\/span>\n        <\/a>\n                    <ul class=\"sub-menu\">\n                <li>\n        <a href=\"#display-name\">\n            <span class=\"title\">display_name<\/span>\n        <\/a>\n            <\/li>\n    <li>\n        <a href=\"#filters\">\n            <span class=\"title\">filters<\/span>\n        <\/a>\n            <\/li>\n    <li>\n        <a href=\"#addons\">\n            <span class=\"title\">addons<\/span>\n        <\/a>\n            <\/li>\n            <\/ul>\n            <\/li>\n    <li>\n        <a href=\"#indexmd\">\n            <span class=\"title\">index.md<\/span>\n        <\/a>\n            <\/li>\n    <li>\n        <a href=\"#revisionyml\">\n            <span class=\"title\">revision.yml<\/span>\n        <\/a>\n            <\/li>\n            <\/ul>\n            <\/li>\n<\/ul><phpdoc-content project=\"codex\" revision=\"master\">\n<p><a name=\"command-line-helper\" class=\"toc-header-link\"><\/a><\/p><h2>Command line helper<\/h2>\n<p>The easiest way to create a new project is using the command line;<\/p>\n<c-code-highlight language=\"bash\" with-line-numbers with-command-line>php artisan codex:create {name?}\n<\/c-code-highlight><p><a name=\"structure\" class=\"toc-header-link\"><\/a><\/p><h2>Structure<\/h2>\n<p>You should follow this structure<\/p>\n<c-code-highlight language=\"php\" with-line-numbers with-command-line>- docs\n    - {name}\n        - config.php\n        - {version}\n            - index.md\n            - menu.yml\n            - other files..\n<\/c-code-highlight><p><a name=\"minimum-required-files\" class=\"toc-header-link\"><\/a><\/p><h2>Minimum required files<\/h2>\n<p><a name=\"configphp\" class=\"toc-header-link\"><\/a><\/p><h3>config.php<\/h3>\n<p>The config file for the project. <\/p>\n<p><a name=\"display-name\" class=\"toc-header-link\"><\/a><\/p><h4>display_name<\/h4>\n<p>The pretty name of the project<\/p>\n<p><strong> Sub menu <\/strong>\nIf you want to have this appear as a sub-menu item in the projects dropdown list. You can use the <code>::<\/code> delimiter.\nFor example <code>Addons :: Auth<\/code>.<\/p>\n<p><a name=\"filters\" class=\"toc-header-link\"><\/a><\/p><h4>filters<\/h4>\n<p>You can define specific filters to be enabled in a project.<\/p>\n<c-code-highlight language=\"php\" with-line-numbers with-command-line>return [\n    'display_name' =&gt; 'Addons :: Auth',\n    'filters' =&gt; [\n        'enabled' =&gt; ['attributes', 'markdown', 'toc'],\n        'toc' =&gt; [\n            'header_link_show'  =&gt; true,\n         ]\n    ]\n];\n<\/c-code-highlight><p>A filter might accept configuration. This should be done as you can see with <code>filters.toc.header_link_show<\/code>. Refer to the documentation of the filter\nto see what is configurable.<\/p>\n<p><a name=\"addons\" class=\"toc-header-link\"><\/a><\/p><h4>addons<\/h4>\n<p>You can define addons to be enabled in a project.<\/p>\n<c-code-highlight language=\"php\" with-line-numbers with-command-line>return [\n    'display_name' =&gt; 'Addons :: Auth',\n    'phpdoc' =&gt; [\n        'enabled'       =&gt; true,\n        'default_class' =&gt; 'Codex\\\\\\Codex',\n    ]\n];\n<\/c-code-highlight><p>A addon might accept configuration. This should be done as you can see with <code>phpdoc.default_class<\/code>. Refer to the documentation of the addon\nto see what is configurable.<\/p>\n<p><a name=\"indexmd\" class=\"toc-header-link\"><\/a><\/p><h3>index.md<\/h3>\n<p>The index markdown file. Every project version requires this index file.<\/p>\n<p><a name=\"revisionyml\" class=\"toc-header-link\"><\/a><\/p><h3>revision.yml<\/h3>\n<p>The revision configuration file. For the sidebar, everything should be placed inside the <code>menu<\/code> node.\nA menu node can contain:<\/p>\n<table class=\"q-table bordered cell-separator\">\n<tr>\n<th align=\"left\">Name<\/th>\n<th align=\"left\">Description<\/th>\n<th align=\"left\">Example<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\"><code>name<\/code><\/td>\n<td align=\"left\">The displayed name<\/td>\n<td align=\"left\"><code>name: Getting Started<\/code><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\"><code>icon<\/code><\/td>\n<td align=\"left\">The font-awesome icon<\/td>\n<td align=\"left\"><code>icon: fa fa-eye<\/code><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\"><code>document<\/code><\/td>\n<td align=\"left\">(optional) If set, the menu item will contain the href link to the specified document<\/td>\n<td align=\"left\"><code>document: index<\/code><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\"><code>children<\/code><\/td>\n<td align=\"left\">(optional) If set, the document will not be a link but will be able to display as sub-menu<\/td>\n<td align=\"left\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\"><code>href<\/code><\/td>\n<td align=\"left\">(optional) If set, the menu item will link to the specified href<\/td>\n<td align=\"left\"><code>href: http:\/\/my-wesbwite.com<\/code><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table><c-code-highlight language=\"yaml\" with-line-numbers with-command-line>menu:\n  - name: Getting started\n    icon: fa fa-eye\n    children:\n\n      - name: Overview\n        document: index\n\n      - name: Todo\n        document: getting-started\/todo\n\n      - name: Installation\n        document: getting-started\/installation\n\n      - name: Configuration\n        document: getting-started\/configuration\n\n      - name: Creating a project\n        document: getting-started\/creating-a-project\n\n\n  - name: Preview pages\n    icon: fa fa-eye\n    children:\n      - name: Typography\n        document: preview-pages\/typography\n\n      - name: ToC Tree\n        document: preview-pages\/toc-tree\n\n      - name: Syntax highlighting\n        document: preview-pages\/syntax-highlight\n<\/c-code-highlight><\/phpdoc-content>","layout":{"header":{"class":{"c-header":true},"style":[],"title":"Codex","revealOnScroll":true,"showTitle":true,"showLeftToggle":true,"showRightToggle":false,"color":"blue-grey-9","menu":[{"_id":"378dd32e-b9ef-4229-abae-cd4163285181","to":{"name":"phpdoc","params":{"project":"codex","revision":"master"}},"type":"router-link","label":"API","sublabel":"Documentation","icon":"fa-file-code-o","color":"secondary"},{"_id":"47db7e3c-f8a7-4525-b9ed-95db552453ff","type":"side-menu","side":"right","children":[{"_id":"72e39f78-af17-4cfd-cdc0-78c2b0396f3e","type":"header","label":"Projects"},{"_id":"14c32c46-97f9-46e2-d8fe-9a4b06e45244","type":"divider"},{"_id":"14ef7ba4-bad7-4607-9a48-c8acc4c4936a","type":"router-link","label":"Test Project","sublabel":"This is a testing project","icon":"fa-book","project":"test-zip-project"},{"_id":"9ea1840a-1214-4bd9-f9b1-1a0b1f3b13a1","type":"router-link","label":"Blade Extensions","sublabel":"Usefull Laravel 5 Blade Directives","icon":"fa-book","project":"blade-extensions"},{"_id":"6001f3b9-808f-4d2b-f0d4-639f36fa97b7","type":"router-link","label":"Codex","sublabel":"Codex is a file-based documentation system build with Laravel 5.5","icon":"fa-book","project":"codex"},{"_id":"e9712f05-efc0-43fe-f868-e80af65501c8","type":"router-link","label":"General Documentation","sublabel":"General documentation for personal reference covering a wide array of subjects","icon":"fa-book","project":"general"}],"label":"Codex","sublabel":"Project","icon":"fa-book"},{"_id":"d1426a54-a56